            <h2 style="text-align:left;">About</h2>
            <p style="text-align:left;" class="lead">
                Neighborly is a crowdsourcing-based resource guide created by Project for Healing, Inc. and
                WeaveTales to help immigrants, refugees, and low-income families in Northeast Florida better
                navigate the resources available in their areas. Neighborly features the locations and information
                on providers of core services such as food, housing, and legal aid. The website is accessible through
                a direct URL: <a href="http://neighborlyguide.org" target="_blank">neighborlyguide.org</a>​ or <a href="http://neighborly.guide" target="_blank">​neighborly.guide​.</a>
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:left;" class="lead">
                Neighborly runs on information crowdsourced by the users and service providers. The website has a submission link where users
                and service providers can add information. Our staff at WeaveTales screen all submissions on a regular basis and publish them online.
                If needed, the person submitting the information or the service providers is contacted to ensure the accuracy and quality of the information
                on the website before making it public. Some of these screening and approval processes take place at the monthly online or offline user meetings
                that WeaveTales hosts. Anyone interested in using or currently using Neighborly is welcome to join the meeting. The dates and locations
                of the meetings may vary each month and are posted on <a href="https://weavetales.org/events" target="_blank">our events calender</a> and
                our <a href="https://twitter.com/neighborlyguide" target="_blank">Twitter</a> @@neighborlyGuide.
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:left;" class="lead">To learn more about Neighborly, please contact us at (904) 990-4821 or <a href="mailto:basma@weavetales.org"> basma@weavetales.org</a>. You can also contact us via <a href="https://weavetales.org/contact-1" target="_blank">website</a></p>
